}}{{TIDTOC|embedded}} ==Overview== A permissive change filing with the FCC suggests that the this '''Belkin F9K1119 v2''' uses hardware identical to the [[Belkin F9K1124 v1]]. Information copied from that device. It's unclear why Belkin claims only 300 Mbps for 802.11n when this is a 3-stream device. Possibly to differentiate from the ''AC1750 DB Wi-Fi Dual-Band AC+ Gigabit Router ([[Belkin F9K1115 v2|F9K1115V2]])'', which is also a Realtek device.
[http://www.belkin.com/us/support-article?articleNum=205537 ''Comparison between the F9K1119 v1 and v2'' from '''Belkin'''] - 2.5A appears to be wrong. The F9K1119v1 is the same hardware (and FCC ID) as the F9K1115v2 ({{fccid|K7SF9K1115V2}}).
Pictures of an actual F9K1119v2 on ebay show 12V/2A and confirm the FCC ID of K7SF9K1124V1.
